1
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:26,294
You are the one who has it.

2
00:01:34,219 --> 00:01:36,012
Are we coming with them later?

3
00:01:36,095 --> 00:01:37,138
It's okay.

4
00:01:59,369 --> 00:02:00,286
FEMALE HEROES

5
00:02:08,545 --> 00:02:09,712
Wait for me outside.

6
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:12,215
I'll just go to the restroom.

7
00:02:22,475 --> 00:02:23,393
Okay.

8
00:02:24,144 --> 00:02:25,270
Wait for me outside.

9
00:02:48,918 --> 00:02:50,086
- Okay.
- All right?

10
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:00,847
- Rene!
- Hey, Tonette!

11
00:03:00,930 --> 00:03:04,475
- They're calling for a faculty meeting.
- What about?

12
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:07,186
I don't know.
Maybe about the student's grades…

13
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:08,980
For you, sir and ma'am!

14
00:03:11,983 --> 00:03:14,736
Sir, do my parents really need to come?

15
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:20,575
- Thanks for the coffee.
- All right.

16
00:03:21,743 --> 00:03:23,620
Your student is nice.

17
00:03:25,079 --> 00:03:26,497
But why do you need her parents?

18
00:03:26,581 --> 00:03:29,208
Why did you give them our coffee?

19
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:31,419
Don't fuss about it.
I'll just buy you another.

20
00:03:34,505 --> 00:03:36,925
- Let's cross the street!
- I'm scared, brother!

21
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:40,011
They won't run us over, I promise!

22
00:03:40,094 --> 00:03:42,347
- You want to cross?
- Yes.

23
00:03:44,557 --> 00:03:45,642
All right, wait.

24
00:03:47,352 --> 00:03:48,937
I'll guide you, but let's hurry.

25
00:03:49,020 --> 00:03:50,021
Go!

26
00:03:52,523 --> 00:03:53,775
Where are you headed?

27
00:03:55,109 --> 00:03:57,237
- Where are you boys headed?
- Just over there.

28
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:58,696
- Where are you going?
- There.

29
00:03:58,780 --> 00:03:59,948
- That way?
- Yes.

30
00:04:00,031 --> 00:04:02,742
Light's green. We can cross now.

31
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:07,288
<i>Pedestrians may now cross…</i>

32
00:04:07,997 --> 00:04:09,958
- We can cross now.
- Okay.

33
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:19,634
or if we have a Scotch,
that'll keep him there longer.

34
00:04:20,134 --> 00:04:22,679
Oh my God. Who put
all this peanut butter here?

35
00:04:23,763 --> 00:04:27,892
Why do we have so many jars here?
Nobody eats this!

36
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:33,606
Bianca, you've been working
for me a long time.

37
00:05:01,217 --> 00:05:04,012
- Tomorrow? I have a trip to Cebu.
- But then, it was kind of long--

38
00:05:04,095 --> 00:05:05,972
- Cebu? What time are you leaving?
- Yes. Tell your Mom.

39
00:05:06,055 --> 00:05:07,473
- Tonight.
- Just for them.

40
00:05:07,557 --> 00:05:08,474
So, you're not coming.

41
00:05:08,558 --> 00:05:12,145
- Mom, you're needed in school tomorrow.
- Gloria! She needs something.

42
00:05:13,104 --> 00:05:15,732
- Can't your dad go?
- He's going to Cebu.

43
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:26,868
Okay, I'm hurrying already.

44
00:05:30,204 --> 00:05:31,247
All right.

45
00:05:32,498 --> 00:05:36,002
Just give him whatever he wants.
I'm leaving.

46
00:05:37,628 --> 00:05:41,924
Babe, please put the groceries
in the fridge, all right?

47
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:44,427
- Please, take care of it.
- What?

48
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:46,721
Put this stuff in the fridge.

49
00:05:46,804 --> 00:05:48,431
Yes, I've got it.

50
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:52,602
Mom?

51
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:14,082
Oh!

52
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:18,252
There's a lot of food
in the cabinet, okay?

53
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:38,481
Concha!

54
00:06:38,564 --> 00:06:40,483
Angel's here!

55
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:41,734
Hey, Angel!

56
00:06:41,818 --> 00:06:43,194
Grandma!

57
00:06:43,277 --> 00:06:44,320
What is it?

58
00:06:44,403 --> 00:06:46,864
Oh, don't! My hands are dirty!

59
00:06:47,448 --> 00:06:49,909
- What brings you here?
- You should've worn gloves.

60
00:06:49,992 --> 00:06:51,452
This is Roger, my friend.

61
00:06:55,164 --> 00:06:56,707
Grandma, come with me to school.

62
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:58,292
What?

63
00:06:58,376 --> 00:06:59,627
I need you there.

64
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:01,963
Why?

65
00:07:02,046 --> 00:07:03,631
The teacher wants to talk.

66
00:07:05,174 --> 00:07:08,052
Why me? What about your parents?

67
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:10,555
Daddy's going to Cebu.

68
00:07:11,973 --> 00:07:13,182
Your mommy?

69
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:14,725
I'm not sure she heard me.

70
00:07:15,601 --> 00:07:16,894
Come on, Grandma.

71
00:07:17,770 --> 00:07:21,732
Angel, I've been gardening.
You see how dirty I am.

72
00:07:21,816 --> 00:07:23,651
Why didn't you wear gloves?

73
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:31,159
The plants won't feel my care
if I don't touch them.

74
00:07:31,242 --> 00:07:35,037
Ma'am, I invited you here

75
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:38,416
to inform you…

76
00:07:38,499 --> 00:07:39,792
MR. RENE B. SANCHEZ
PROFESSOR

77
00:07:39,876 --> 00:07:43,296
…that Angel's grades are failing.

78
00:07:44,672 --> 00:07:49,302
She can take remedial classes,
but maybe that's not enough.

79
00:07:49,385 --> 00:07:55,641
She needs to take summer classes
in math and in chemistry.

80
00:07:59,770 --> 00:08:01,147
Angel.

81
00:08:01,939 --> 00:08:05,026
You have to pass the summer classes
so you won't have to repeat Grade 12.

82
00:08:07,028 --> 00:08:08,196
All right.

83
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:13,117
Actually, if you pass this summer,

84
00:08:17,872 --> 00:08:20,791
That's what's nice about it.

85
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:22,919
You just need to pass these two subjects.

86
00:08:23,002 --> 00:08:23,961
All right.

87
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:29,967
Thank you.

88
00:08:30,468 --> 00:08:31,761
Angel.

89
00:08:31,844 --> 00:08:32,929
Let's go.

90
00:09:30,861 --> 00:09:32,280
When is your flight?

91
00:09:33,281 --> 00:09:34,407
Tonight.

92
00:09:36,909 --> 00:09:38,119
So?

93
00:09:38,786 --> 00:09:40,162
What do we do about Angel?

94
00:09:42,456 --> 00:09:44,709
Obviously, you take charge of her.

95
00:09:44,792 --> 00:09:47,295
You know we have to deal
with Angel's issues.

96
00:09:47,878 --> 00:09:49,672
She'll have more years of schooling.

97
00:09:52,216 --> 00:09:54,260
You're the mother. You take care of her.
What do I know about that?

98
00:09:54,343 --> 00:09:56,262
Just because I am the mother?

99
00:09:56,345 --> 00:09:58,139
What about you? Aren't you her father?

100
00:09:58,222 --> 00:09:59,974
You have a responsibility to her.

101
00:10:00,766 --> 00:10:02,226
Do I need to carry everything?

102
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:04,186
We both made her.

103
00:10:06,772 --> 00:10:09,942
Why would you push that problem on me?

104
00:10:10,026 --> 00:10:12,737
You're the mother.
I should focus on my job.

105
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:15,865
You should manage the home, not me.

106
00:10:15,948 --> 00:10:17,783
I work too!

107
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:20,828
Just because we're both working,
you won't attend to your child?

108
00:10:20,911 --> 00:10:24,040
So when it comes to caring for her,
I should do it solo?

109
00:10:24,123 --> 00:10:26,417
That's your duty. Don't force it on me.

110
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:28,252
Don't forget our roles.

111
00:10:28,836 --> 00:10:30,671
I forget--

112
00:10:30,755 --> 00:10:33,257
My God, Raymund!

113
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:38,846
From the start,
you didn't participate in rearing Angel.

114
00:10:38,929 --> 00:10:40,890
It's always me, the mother.

115
00:10:40,973 --> 00:10:42,183
Why is that?

116
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:44,894
Do your part now.

117
00:10:44,977 --> 00:10:46,354
Give me--

118
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:56,364
Am I asking for too much?

119
00:10:58,074 --> 00:11:01,202
Oh, my God. Can I do the asking now?

120
00:11:03,287 --> 00:11:05,039
What are you saying?
I've stayed here for so long.

121
00:11:05,122 --> 00:11:07,792
All that time, I was here for you.
What am I to you?

122
00:11:07,875 --> 00:11:08,709
Was I useless?

123
00:11:08,793 --> 00:11:12,171
Yes, you were here.
You go in and out of the house…

124
00:11:12,254 --> 00:11:17,218
without even asking how we're doing,
how we're getting by on our days!

125
00:11:23,224 --> 00:11:25,643
How you talk! Who stayed home, huh?

126
00:11:25,726 --> 00:11:27,019
- Who was there?
- Exactly.

127
00:11:27,103 --> 00:11:31,399
- I'm the one who's always here.
- Even on weekends, you weren't home!

128
00:11:31,482 --> 00:11:34,902
I'm working. Come on!
You were the one who's not here!

129
00:11:34,985 --> 00:11:37,488
- You take care of Angel now!
- That's no excuse!

130
00:11:38,197 --> 00:11:40,157
You know what? That will do her good.

131
00:11:40,241 --> 00:11:44,203
Bring her to Cebu with you.
Give her a fresh start.

132
00:11:44,286 --> 00:11:46,247
She can make new friends.

133
00:11:46,330 --> 00:11:50,584
She doesn't need to be here.
I have nothing left for her.

134
00:11:50,668 --> 00:11:52,837
I have given her so much.

135
00:11:53,421 --> 00:11:55,756
I've had enough.

136
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:58,175
I'm done with Angel. I'm done with you.

137
00:11:58,259 --> 00:11:59,969
I'm done with this kind of life.

138
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:02,430
Your turn. Do your part.

139
00:12:02,513 --> 00:12:03,806
For God's sake!

140
00:12:04,723 --> 00:12:06,100
I'm done.

141
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:53,189
<i>The subscriber cannot be reached.</i>
<i>Please try again later.</i>

142
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:17,630
Where are you? Why weren't you picking up?

143
00:13:17,713 --> 00:13:21,300
<i>I was with my mom.</i>
<i>We went shopping. We ate out.</i>

144
00:13:21,383 --> 00:13:23,093
Why didn't you text me?

145
00:13:23,177 --> 00:13:24,595
<i>Ran out of battery.</i>

146
00:13:24,678 --> 00:13:27,348
Ran out? How come you can text me now?

147
00:13:27,431 --> 00:13:29,099
Nonsense.

148
00:13:29,183 --> 00:13:32,186
<i>Of course, I tried to turn on</i>
<i>the phone to reply to you.</i>

149
00:13:32,269 --> 00:13:35,105
Now you're annoyed,
when this is the only time we can talk.

150
00:13:35,189 --> 00:13:37,233
I wanted to tell you something!

151
00:13:37,316 --> 00:13:38,901
Never mind!

152
00:13:49,078 --> 00:13:52,623
- What did you get?
- Why do I have a tank top?

153
00:13:54,583 --> 00:13:56,835
- I can't open mine.
- I got a tank top.

154
00:13:56,919 --> 00:13:58,337
Open it. Hurry!

155
00:13:58,420 --> 00:14:01,507
- Open it. Help me!
- Let's see.

156
00:14:02,383 --> 00:14:04,552
You're so excited for it.

157
00:14:04,635 --> 00:14:05,678
Wait, what's this?

158
00:14:10,057 --> 00:14:13,102
This should be mine! Take mine!

159
00:14:31,829 --> 00:14:33,122
Concha?

160
00:14:33,956 --> 00:14:36,125
Angel will be staying
here with us for now.

161
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:37,543
Oh?

162
00:14:38,586 --> 00:14:39,795
What happened?

163
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:42,673
Let me stay here, Grandma.

164
00:14:43,841 --> 00:14:45,009
All right.

165
00:14:45,092 --> 00:14:46,719
Same room as always.

166
00:14:46,802 --> 00:14:48,220
Bring your luggage there.

167
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:49,179
Sorry?

168
00:14:50,472 --> 00:14:53,517
I said bring your things to your room.

169
00:14:53,601 --> 00:14:54,560
All right.

170
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:58,522
Anyway, what happened to your school?

171
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:00,232
It's all settled.

172
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:07,740
All right, take your things upstairs.

173
00:15:13,954 --> 00:15:18,876
This is my grandma's house.
I'll give you a tour.

174
00:15:18,959 --> 00:15:20,669
Here, look!

175
00:15:25,591 --> 00:15:27,801
Check this out. So cute!

176
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:29,803
Does this still work?

177
00:15:33,015 --> 00:15:36,769
Here's a painting of my darling grandma.

178
00:15:36,852 --> 00:15:38,437
Hi, Grandma.

179
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:43,317
And then here, we have… the family photos!

180
00:15:47,571 --> 00:15:50,032
We look alike, right? Beautiful.

181
00:15:55,704 --> 00:16:01,168
Isn't she perfect?

182
00:16:01,251 --> 00:16:03,837
My grandma is so beautiful.

183
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:09,093
See where I inherited my looks from?

184
00:16:09,176 --> 00:16:10,594
What's this?

185
00:16:11,887 --> 00:16:14,682
Is this thing working?

186
00:16:16,725 --> 00:16:18,686
How do you use this?

187
00:16:19,269 --> 00:16:20,646
Never mind. I might break it.

188
00:16:20,729 --> 00:16:23,774
This way leads back to the living room.

189
00:16:25,901 --> 00:16:29,697
See how huge Grandma's house is? My gosh!

190
00:16:34,868 --> 00:16:37,246
So, that's it! That's Grandma's house.

191
00:16:40,165 --> 00:16:41,917
No bashing, okay?

192
00:16:49,299 --> 00:16:53,429
Help me catch one.
We'll have chicken soup later.

193
00:16:54,805 --> 00:16:56,890
- Okay.
- Go on.

194
00:16:57,725 --> 00:17:00,477
Pick a fat one.

195
00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:02,980
Wait.

196
00:17:03,063 --> 00:17:04,314
The tail.

197
00:17:08,610 --> 00:17:13,073
Wait, I'll let it relax a bit. Wait.

198
00:17:14,158 --> 00:17:15,534
It might poop on me!

199
00:17:15,617 --> 00:17:16,994
Wait.

200
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:20,122
Doggie?

201
00:17:20,205 --> 00:17:22,416
Be a good boy! Wait!

202
00:17:22,499 --> 00:17:24,418
- Wait.
- Give it to me.

203
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:28,589
- Finally! I got it!
- See?

204
00:17:28,672 --> 00:17:30,257
We got it.

205
00:17:30,340 --> 00:17:32,342
Now you know how to do it!

206
00:17:32,426 --> 00:17:35,929
Grandma, why do you care for them
if you're just going to eat them?

207
00:17:36,013 --> 00:17:41,226
Their purpose is to nourish us.

208
00:17:42,478 --> 00:17:48,358
It's not selfishness.
It's the circle of life.

209
00:17:48,442 --> 00:17:51,153
Grandma Ninay, how long
have you been here?

210
00:17:55,657 --> 00:17:57,534
A very long time.

211
00:17:57,618 --> 00:18:03,040
Imagine, I took care of your grandmother.

212
00:18:06,502 --> 00:18:08,670
And your mother, too.

213
00:18:09,421 --> 00:18:11,548
When you were born,

214
00:18:12,257 --> 00:18:14,718
I also took care of you.

215
00:18:16,011 --> 00:18:17,387
Do you know that?

216
00:18:17,888 --> 00:18:22,351
But only for three years,

217
00:18:22,935 --> 00:18:25,854
because your family moved.

218
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:32,569
When did Grandpa die?

219
00:18:34,988 --> 00:18:37,866
- Come again, child?
- When did Grandpa die?

220
00:18:38,659 --> 00:18:41,495
You were…

221
00:18:42,371 --> 00:18:46,792
You were about five when he passed.

222
00:18:48,168 --> 00:18:49,378
What did he die of?

223
00:18:50,212 --> 00:18:54,466
He liked eating

224
00:18:55,717 --> 00:18:59,054
unhealthy food.

225
00:18:59,138 --> 00:19:03,016
He loved eating stewed pork
and grilled pork.

226
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:05,686
So he had a heart attack.

227
00:19:05,769 --> 00:19:10,899
So stop eating junk food.
It's not good for you.

228
00:19:11,650 --> 00:19:15,612
That's why I always cook vegetables
for your grandma.

229
00:19:15,696 --> 00:19:19,533
This is good for our health.

230
00:19:20,617 --> 00:19:24,079
We don't have that at home
because my mom doesn't cook that.

231
00:19:29,376 --> 00:19:30,836
I'll open it.

232
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:38,385
Why did you leave the gate open?

233
00:19:39,469 --> 00:19:40,679
Hey, Angel.

234
00:19:41,346 --> 00:19:44,516
You didn't even tell me you're here.

235
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:46,602
If I hadn't seen your post,

236
00:19:46,685 --> 00:19:49,313
I wouldn't have known
that you're with your Grandma.

237
00:19:50,063 --> 00:19:51,398
I just visited Grandma.

238
00:19:51,481 --> 00:19:54,651
You could've told me that.
I'd have permitted you.

239
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:58,739
I couldn't attend to my clients
because I was worried about you.

240
00:20:07,372 --> 00:20:10,751
- You want rice?
- Yes, just a bit.

241
00:20:11,919 --> 00:20:15,422
- One more.
- I don't eat rice that much now.

242
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:18,759
Here, Angel.

243
00:20:20,135 --> 00:20:21,261
Hey, here.

244
00:20:21,345 --> 00:20:22,971
- Ninay!
- Here!

245
00:20:23,055 --> 00:20:25,182
Have some of this chicken soup.

246
00:20:25,265 --> 00:20:29,311
- That looks wonderful.
- Eat while it's hot. Here.

247
00:20:30,062 --> 00:20:32,022
That's delicious and nutritious.

248
00:20:32,522 --> 00:20:34,066
Hey, Gloria.

249
00:20:34,149 --> 00:20:36,610
Angel said you don't cook vegetables.

250
00:20:36,693 --> 00:20:37,986
That's wrong.

251
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:40,239
But she's the one who won't eat veggies!

252
00:20:40,322 --> 00:20:43,116
Angel, eat vegetables. You heard Ninay.

253
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,660
- Make her eat vegetables.
- Ninay.

254
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:46,745
Ninay, sit down.

255
00:20:46,828 --> 00:20:50,040
- Join us for lunch.
- Later. I need to clean the kitchen.

256
00:20:50,123 --> 00:20:51,500
Go ahead.

257
00:20:52,251 --> 00:20:54,002
Give me some soup.

258
00:20:54,503 --> 00:20:55,504
Angel…

259
00:20:59,758 --> 00:21:03,428
That's yummy for sure.
Do you cook chicken soup, Gloria?

260
00:21:03,512 --> 00:21:07,891
I don't cook often
because I'm always at work.

261
00:21:08,433 --> 00:21:10,727
So this one mostly eats take-out.

262
00:21:11,228 --> 00:21:15,983
You should learn to cook.
Ask Ninay to teach you while you're here.

263
00:21:16,066 --> 00:21:20,404
Ninay, thank you for cooking.
It's delicious.

264
00:21:21,029 --> 00:21:22,447
It's perfect.

265
00:21:27,494 --> 00:21:31,498
Gloria, have you sold
the in Solar Ventures, Inc properties?

266
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:35,627
I sold one.

267
00:21:36,878 --> 00:21:39,172
- One?
- But that was a big account.

268
00:21:39,256 --> 00:21:40,299
Just one?

269
00:21:40,382 --> 00:21:44,052
Those offered in Tagaytay
are hot properties.

270
00:21:45,012 --> 00:21:50,142
Well, I have other prospects

271
00:21:50,225 --> 00:21:52,477
under negotiation already.

272
00:21:53,061 --> 00:21:57,149
Those properties are great,
but they're also expensive, Ma,

273
00:21:57,941 --> 00:22:00,902
so people have to consider it,
but I'm pretty sure…

274
00:22:01,695 --> 00:22:03,071
they'll decide to buy it.

275
00:22:03,155 --> 00:22:07,367
- I'll close those deals soon.
- You've been selling those for a while.

276
00:22:07,451 --> 00:22:11,038
How can you become the top broker
if you don't sell more?

277
00:22:17,419 --> 00:22:21,173
How's Raymund? How's his work?

278
00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:27,095
He's concentrating on Cebu.

279
00:22:27,179 --> 00:22:32,100
He might stay there,
since he opened a business.

280
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:33,393
That's good.

281
00:22:36,021 --> 00:22:36,855
Mom--

282
00:22:38,356 --> 00:22:40,400
Grandma? What's the matter?

283
00:22:40,484 --> 00:22:42,360
- Ma?
- What's happening?

284
00:22:42,444 --> 00:22:44,154
Ma?

285
00:22:44,738 --> 00:22:45,655
What's happening to her?

286
00:22:45,739 --> 00:22:46,865
Ma?

287
00:22:46,948 --> 00:22:48,283
- Ninay!
- It hurts!

288
00:22:49,284 --> 00:22:50,535
Ninay!

289
00:22:50,619 --> 00:22:54,206
Ninay, bring Mama's medicine here.

290
00:22:54,831 --> 00:22:56,041
Ma?

291
00:22:56,625 --> 00:22:57,834
Let's go to your room.

292
00:22:58,376 --> 00:22:59,377
It hurts!

293
00:22:59,461 --> 00:23:01,755
- Ninay!
- Ninay, the medicine!

294
00:23:01,838 --> 00:23:03,465
- The medicine, please!
- It hurts!

295
00:23:03,548 --> 00:23:06,343
Come, you should lie down.

296
00:23:11,264 --> 00:23:12,432
Ma?

297
00:23:13,183 --> 00:23:15,852
Is the medicine working?
Are you still in pain?

298
00:23:25,153 --> 00:23:26,279
Mom?

299
00:23:27,072 --> 00:23:28,323
What's Grandma's illness?

300
00:23:34,454 --> 00:23:35,997
She has cancer.

301
00:23:39,918 --> 00:23:41,503
Pancreatic cancer.

302
00:23:44,714 --> 00:23:46,007
Will she get better?

303
00:23:51,179 --> 00:23:53,390
She's given a few months to live.

304
00:23:56,143 --> 00:23:57,352
I need to go.

305
00:23:58,228 --> 00:23:59,604
Mom, I'll stay here for bit.

306
00:24:01,481 --> 00:24:02,732
Up to you.

307
00:24:05,443 --> 00:24:07,028
You look after her, all right?

308
00:24:11,992 --> 00:24:13,160
I have to go.

309
00:25:24,189 --> 00:25:25,273
Mom…

310
00:25:27,108 --> 00:25:28,818
I won't take the summer class for now.

311
00:25:29,486 --> 00:25:31,446
I'll stay here to take care of Grandma.

312
00:25:31,988 --> 00:25:34,491
<i>All right, you look after her.</i>

313
00:25:34,574 --> 00:25:37,577
<i>Paul and I are going to Baguio.</i>

314
00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:43,583
Okay. Bye.

315
00:27:33,860 --> 00:27:35,403
Grandma, who are you speaking to?

316
00:27:39,783 --> 00:27:40,867
No one.

317
00:27:44,704 --> 00:27:47,082
Why are you still up? It's late.

318
00:27:48,375 --> 00:27:49,709
Let's go to sleep.

319
00:27:50,835 --> 00:27:52,003
Come.

320
00:28:43,805 --> 00:28:45,515
Grandma, what are you doing?

321
00:28:47,434 --> 00:28:48,768
Oh! Nothing.

322
00:28:49,519 --> 00:28:50,854
Just looking at my prom dress.

323
00:28:52,939 --> 00:28:54,315
Here's the other one.

324
00:28:54,399 --> 00:28:55,316
This one.

325
00:28:56,609 --> 00:28:58,111
This is my prom dress before.

326
00:28:58,194 --> 00:28:59,654
Let me see it on you.

327
00:29:00,196 --> 00:29:01,364
Wow.

328
00:29:01,448 --> 00:29:03,324
- Looks like it'll fit you.
- Grandma.

329
00:29:03,408 --> 00:29:06,077
Turn around! I'm sure it suits you.

330
00:29:07,036 --> 00:29:08,955
Looks beautiful.

331
00:29:09,622 --> 00:29:11,416
Looks like it'll fit you.

332
00:29:11,499 --> 00:29:14,377
Angel, try it on.

333
00:29:14,461 --> 00:29:17,213
- What?
- I want to see you in it.

334
00:29:19,090 --> 00:29:21,468
All right, I'll put in on in my room.

335
00:29:23,219 --> 00:29:24,721
Okay, thank you! Good night.

336
00:30:39,879 --> 00:30:43,091
YOUR GRANDMA IS SO ADORABLE!
MISS MINE NOW

337
00:30:43,174 --> 00:30:47,220
<i>Somehow there is assurance</i>
<i>that our people are being taken care of…</i>

338
00:30:47,303 --> 00:30:50,723
<i>The President likewise guaranteed</i>
<i>the support of our government</i>

339
00:30:50,807 --> 00:30:53,935
<i>to all affected families,</i>
<i>especially those who lost their homes</i>

340
00:30:54,018 --> 00:30:56,938
<i>to this devastating flood.</i>

341
00:30:59,357 --> 00:31:03,444
<i>Ten-year-old girl rescues</i>
<i>drowning cat during flood.</i>

342
00:31:04,445 --> 00:31:08,449
<i>In the middle of waist-deep</i>
<i>flood waters in Barangay San Isidro,</i>

343
00:31:09,450 --> 00:31:13,663
{\an8}<i>a ten-year-old girl named Anna</i>
<i>became a hero when she risked her life</i>

344
00:31:13,746 --> 00:31:15,874
{\an8}<i>to save a drowning cat.</i>

345
00:31:15,957 --> 00:31:16,916
{\an8}‪LOW PRESSURE SETS COURSE FOR REGION

346
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,209
{\an8}<i>Holding on to a rope--</i>

347
00:31:20,253 --> 00:31:21,254
Grandma?

348
00:31:28,344 --> 00:31:29,304
Grandma?

349
00:32:06,341 --> 00:32:09,052
CATHERINE DE LEON

350
00:32:16,309 --> 00:32:20,980
TO CONCHA
TONIGHT, I CAN WRITE THE SADDEST LINES…

351
00:32:21,064 --> 00:32:24,901
TO CATHERINE

352
00:33:08,027 --> 00:33:14,659
{\an8}DEAREST CATHERINE
I DON'T KNOW IF YOU'LL EVER READ THIS

353
00:34:11,299 --> 00:34:12,300
Grandma…

354
00:34:14,802 --> 00:34:16,012
Who's Catherine?

355
00:34:44,832 --> 00:34:47,126
Grandma, do you need help?

356
00:34:47,210 --> 00:34:48,252
Yes, sure.

357
00:34:58,096 --> 00:35:00,431
Grandma, how did you meet Catherine?

358
00:35:08,231 --> 00:35:10,608
Catherine was my high school teacher.

359
00:35:12,819 --> 00:35:16,823
But we became close
because of a planting activity.

360
00:35:16,906 --> 00:35:18,908
She is fond of plants too.

361
00:35:23,037 --> 00:35:25,331
<i>My life revolved around school</i>
<i>and home then.</i>

362
00:35:26,249 --> 00:35:30,795
<i>Maybe I was the only student</i>
<i>who got excited to attend class every day</i>

363
00:35:30,878 --> 00:35:33,005
<i>because I got to see her.</i>

364
00:35:33,089 --> 00:35:34,549
<i>Catherine.</i>

365
00:35:39,846 --> 00:35:41,764
<i>She was alone.</i>

366
00:35:43,182 --> 00:35:48,146
An adopted child,
though treated like family.

367
00:35:50,731 --> 00:35:52,567
She was like a sister to me.

368
00:35:53,818 --> 00:35:55,319
{\an8}<i>More than a sister.</i>

369
00:35:57,363 --> 00:35:59,407
<i>With her, I could show my true self.</i>

370
00:36:01,033 --> 00:36:03,202
<i>She guided my life.</i>

371
00:36:08,416 --> 00:36:13,171
<i>That was the happiest time in my life…</i>

372
00:36:14,213 --> 00:36:17,258
<i>The days when we were together.</i>

373
00:36:31,939 --> 00:36:33,316
What happened afterwards?

374
00:36:37,570 --> 00:36:39,947
My father had me transferred
to another school.

375
00:36:40,740 --> 00:36:42,158
Before I graduated.

376
00:36:43,618 --> 00:36:46,495
He didn't want me to be close to her.

377
00:36:48,080 --> 00:36:50,333
He said she was a distraction
to my studies.

378
00:37:02,678 --> 00:37:05,181
Grandma, do you want me to find Catherine?

379
00:37:21,989 --> 00:37:23,241
Hey, let's go!

380
00:37:24,575 --> 00:37:26,410
- Hurry up, bud.
- Wait, I'll just finish this game.

381
00:37:26,494 --> 00:37:27,745
No need for that.

382
00:37:27,828 --> 00:37:29,163
Why did you have to play here?

383
00:37:29,247 --> 00:37:30,998
Our home WiFi got cut off.

384
00:37:31,916 --> 00:37:35,378
Roger, about what I told you…
Can you drive me somewhere?

385
00:37:36,254 --> 00:37:39,423
That's a tough request.
I need to borrow the car from Mommy.

386
00:37:40,049 --> 00:37:42,093
And I only have a student's license.

387
00:37:46,681 --> 00:37:47,556
Come on.

388
00:37:48,182 --> 00:37:50,559
I'm almost done.

389
00:37:53,229 --> 00:37:55,773
I'll drive, as long
as we go back immediately.

390
00:38:00,111 --> 00:38:04,448
You worrywart!
Why, am I not your girlfriend?

391
00:38:04,949 --> 00:38:09,453
This is the only time I asked you a favor.
Me, I always treated you.

392
00:38:15,167 --> 00:38:18,087
True, but we need to go back immediately
because my mom might get mad.

393
00:38:18,170 --> 00:38:20,673
She uses this van
for her delivery business.

394
00:38:34,562 --> 00:38:38,357
<i>Even if I lose my way</i>

395
00:38:38,441 --> 00:38:43,154
<i>I'll find the road leading to you</i>

396
00:38:44,613 --> 00:38:47,408
<i>You're my destination</i>

397
00:38:48,701 --> 00:38:55,166
<i>It might get dim</i>
<i>But you'll still be my light</i>

398
00:38:55,249 --> 00:39:01,422
<i>Oh, oh, oh, oh</i>

399
00:39:01,505 --> 00:39:07,219
<i>Why do I thirst for your dance?</i>
<i>Why is it always you?</i>

400
00:39:09,680 --> 00:39:15,061
<i>I won't let go, I'm yours, always yours</i>

401
00:39:15,853 --> 00:39:21,108
<i>I'm cold, come here, stay with me</i>

402
00:39:28,199 --> 00:39:30,534
DR. LYDIA M. PROFETA
BUILDING

403
00:39:46,133 --> 00:39:48,594
Sir, where's the faculty?

404
00:39:48,677 --> 00:39:51,764
Where do they keep the records
of retired teachers?

405
00:39:53,432 --> 00:39:58,479
Just go that way,
then you'll see it, ma'am.

406
00:39:59,063 --> 00:40:00,231
All right, thank you.

407
00:40:00,314 --> 00:40:01,273
All right, ma'am.

408
00:40:05,903 --> 00:40:07,738
I'm looking for Catherine de Leon, sir.

409
00:40:07,822 --> 00:40:09,073
Catherine de Leon.

410
00:40:09,156 --> 00:40:12,284
What year was she here?

411
00:40:13,994 --> 00:40:15,913
1974 or thereabouts.

412
00:40:16,455 --> 00:40:17,706
1974…

413
00:40:17,790 --> 00:40:19,375
- Fatima?
- Yes, sir.

414
00:40:19,458 --> 00:40:24,422
Look for the records of Teacher Catherine…

415
00:40:24,505 --> 00:40:26,340
- Okay.
- de Leon.

416
00:40:26,424 --> 00:40:28,676
Year 1974.

417
00:40:31,387 --> 00:40:35,391
You know, there's only a few

418
00:40:35,975 --> 00:40:40,146
old-timer teachers like me here.

419
00:40:40,229 --> 00:40:44,692
Many teachers transfer to private schools.

420
00:40:44,775 --> 00:40:47,361
There are more
opportunities there, I guess.

421
00:40:48,112 --> 00:40:54,660
So, you won't find
a lot of old-timers here now.

422
00:40:57,580 --> 00:41:00,082
- You found Catherine's?
- Yes, these are her records.

423
00:41:01,333 --> 00:41:02,877
Catherine de Leon.

424
00:41:09,341 --> 00:41:12,511
Oh, I remember now.

425
00:41:13,012 --> 00:41:18,684
Cathy! Yes, she was a teacher here.

426
00:41:20,478 --> 00:41:24,690
Wait. It says here her address is 827…

427
00:41:24,773 --> 00:41:28,319
- 827 B…
- B…

428
00:41:28,944 --> 00:41:30,988
Peñafrancia Street…

429
00:41:31,071 --> 00:41:32,615
Peñafrancia Street. Okay.

430
00:41:32,698 --> 00:41:36,327
- Barangay Pio del Pilar…
- Barangay Pio?

431
00:41:36,410 --> 00:41:38,037
- Yes.
- Del Pilar. All right.

432
00:41:38,120 --> 00:41:39,622
- Paco, Manila.
- Paco, Manila.

433
00:41:39,705 --> 00:41:41,874
Oh, okay.

434
00:41:41,957 --> 00:41:45,044
Ma'am Cathy…

435
00:41:45,127 --> 00:41:51,342
I remember she used to teach
English literature here.

436
00:41:53,802 --> 00:41:56,639
As far as I recollect,

437
00:41:57,890 --> 00:42:00,893
she used to sit in that area.

438
00:42:01,393 --> 00:42:06,315
That's her favorite spot
when she's doing research.

439
00:42:31,215 --> 00:42:33,801
This is Catherine's classroom.

440
00:42:34,426 --> 00:42:36,470
This is where she teaches.

441
00:42:36,554 --> 00:42:38,430
<i>‪…but I had lost her.</i>

442
00:43:22,516 --> 00:43:26,186
Why do you need to find her?
They're just friends.

443
00:43:27,021 --> 00:43:29,315
They are more than friends.

444
00:43:29,857 --> 00:43:31,817
More than friends?

445
00:43:31,900 --> 00:43:34,236
What do you mean?
They're lovers or something?

446
00:43:34,945 --> 00:43:36,113
Yes?

447
00:43:39,325 --> 00:43:42,828
They've had a deep bond
since they were young.

448
00:43:42,911 --> 00:43:44,496
Not like you. You're shallow.

449
00:43:44,580 --> 00:43:45,456
Huh?

450
00:43:46,915 --> 00:43:47,958
You fuck!

451
00:43:48,042 --> 00:43:49,418
Moron!

452
00:43:49,501 --> 00:43:50,628
Hey!

453
00:43:50,711 --> 00:43:52,004
- Are you an idiot?
- Hey, hey!

454
00:43:52,087 --> 00:43:53,547
Can't you see where you're going?

455
00:43:53,631 --> 00:43:56,884
- Roger, enough! Stop that!
- Use your eyes, shitbrain! Fuck you!

456
00:43:57,468 --> 00:44:00,095
What if this had gotten a scratch?
If he'd hit us.

457
00:44:01,972 --> 00:44:03,932
- My mother will kill me.
- You blockhead, if we had gotten caught,

458
00:44:04,016 --> 00:44:05,100
you don't have a license!

459
00:44:05,184 --> 00:44:07,269
Exactly, I have no license,
so I'm being careful,

460
00:44:07,353 --> 00:44:09,188
but he has to bump me!

461
00:44:09,772 --> 00:44:11,231
Street moron.

462
00:44:13,275 --> 00:44:14,276
That was close.

463
00:44:32,628 --> 00:44:34,922
We couldn't take care
of Catherine anymore,

464
00:44:35,005 --> 00:44:38,258
so we brought her
to a retirement home five years ago.

465
00:44:40,803 --> 00:44:44,014
We can't give her the proper care.

466
00:44:44,098 --> 00:44:46,058
I have health issues.

467
00:44:46,684 --> 00:44:50,187
These stairs? It's too steep for me.

468
00:44:50,270 --> 00:44:55,442
That's why I often sleep downstairs,
on that sofa.

469
00:45:04,785 --> 00:45:07,037
It's just the two of us here.

470
00:45:07,121 --> 00:45:10,040
Our kids have gone abroad, too.

471
00:45:13,085 --> 00:45:15,629
Eat some more.

472
00:45:15,712 --> 00:45:18,632
Take this with you, too.

473
00:45:19,216 --> 00:45:22,136
Which home did you bring
Ma'am Catherine to?

474
00:45:22,219 --> 00:45:24,930
She's in Asilo, in Sta. Ana.

475
00:45:28,267 --> 00:45:29,351
All right.

476
00:45:29,435 --> 00:45:30,436
Eat.

477
00:45:30,519 --> 00:45:32,855
- Thank you.
- Eat more.

478
00:45:32,938 --> 00:45:35,232
These are all for you.

479
00:45:35,315 --> 00:45:37,568
- Wrap it and take it home.
- Come on, enough of that…

480
00:45:37,651 --> 00:45:39,528
So you'll have snacks on your way.

481
00:45:39,611 --> 00:45:41,780
- We need to go now.
- Are you sure?

482
00:45:41,864 --> 00:45:43,866
Yes, sir, we already found the place.

483
00:45:43,949 --> 00:45:46,118
- Thank you!
- Take care, then.

484
00:45:46,201 --> 00:45:47,035
‪Bye-bye.

485
00:45:59,298 --> 00:46:05,095
ASILO DE SAN VICENTE DE PAVL

486
00:46:21,487 --> 00:46:23,030
Sister Fely.

487
00:46:23,113 --> 00:46:24,198
Please come in.

488
00:46:27,034 --> 00:46:29,953
This is Angel Torres,
the one I told you about.

489
00:46:30,871 --> 00:46:34,625
You can leave them here. Have a seat.

490
00:46:41,465 --> 00:46:44,134
How are you related to Catherine de Leon?

491
00:46:45,052 --> 00:46:46,803
She's my grandmother's friend.

492
00:46:46,887 --> 00:46:49,097
They haven't seen each other
for a long time.

493
00:46:50,349 --> 00:46:52,643
Why are you looking for her?

494
00:46:54,603 --> 00:46:58,106
I'm not sure, but they haven't
seen each other for years.

495
00:46:59,942 --> 00:47:01,401
Do you have an ID, my child?

496
00:47:28,178 --> 00:47:30,305
How did you find Catherine?

497
00:47:33,100 --> 00:47:34,851
We searched the internet.

498
00:47:35,519 --> 00:47:37,145
It's easy nowadays.

499
00:47:37,646 --> 00:47:41,066
- Have you heard of AI?
- No.

500
00:47:41,149 --> 00:47:45,279
You type the name of the person
you're looking for,

501
00:47:45,362 --> 00:47:48,365
and the information will appear.

502
00:47:49,032 --> 00:47:52,369
- Really? That's wonderful.
- Yes.

503
00:47:53,328 --> 00:47:57,207
That's how I found my father.

504
00:47:57,291 --> 00:48:00,711
Now I can easily stalk him online.

505
00:48:30,991 --> 00:48:33,452
- Good morning, Sister Fely!
- Good morning.

506
00:48:33,535 --> 00:48:34,620
This is Grandma Concha.

507
00:48:34,703 --> 00:48:36,872
- Grandma, this is Sister Fely.
- Good morning.

508
00:48:36,955 --> 00:48:38,665
Good morning to you.

509
00:48:38,749 --> 00:48:41,627
Thank you for allowing us to visit.

510
00:48:41,710 --> 00:48:42,961
You're welcome.

511
00:48:43,045 --> 00:48:49,926
The relatives and friends
of our patients can visit anytime.

512
00:48:50,010 --> 00:48:50,886
Sister, what is going on?

513
00:48:50,969 --> 00:48:57,559
Sorry, we have many people here now
because we have lots of activities.

514
00:48:57,643 --> 00:49:00,604
We have an event today.

515
00:49:00,687 --> 00:49:06,026
- Can we enter now?
- Of course, you can go inside.

516
00:49:06,109 --> 00:49:11,073
- Can my grandma join that?
- If she wants to, why not?

517
00:49:11,156 --> 00:49:12,032
‪All right, then.

518
00:49:12,115 --> 00:49:13,408
- Do we need to sign--
- Looks fun!

519
00:49:13,492 --> 00:49:15,077
Yes, it's fun!

520
00:49:15,702 --> 00:49:21,333
No need for that.
You don't need to show an ID.

521
00:49:21,416 --> 00:49:23,001
- Up to what hour can we stay?
- Thank you.

522
00:49:23,085 --> 00:49:26,338
As long as you like. It's fine.

523
00:49:26,421 --> 00:49:29,091
You can park over there.

524
00:49:29,174 --> 00:49:30,467
All right.

525
00:49:30,550 --> 00:49:34,137
- Thank you, Sister.
- No problem, child.

526
00:50:47,210 --> 00:50:48,336
Catherine?

527
00:52:42,117 --> 00:52:45,120
Is that old telephone still working?

528
00:52:55,005 --> 00:52:57,757
Before she lost her memory,

529
00:52:58,425 --> 00:52:59,926
she said we shouldn't take it away

530
00:53:00,010 --> 00:53:02,345
because she's waiting for a call.

531
00:53:13,273 --> 00:53:16,818
We see no problem
with your request, Ms. Concha,

532
00:53:16,902 --> 00:53:19,571
and you're on good terms with Mr. Durian.

533
00:53:19,654 --> 00:53:22,574
You only need to sign a waiver

534
00:53:22,657 --> 00:53:26,995
that states that we are no longer
responsible for Ms. Catherine's care.

535
00:53:27,078 --> 00:53:28,246
I will.

536
00:53:28,997 --> 00:53:30,624
Thank you, Sister.

537
00:53:30,707 --> 00:53:32,375
- Thank you, Concha.
- You're welcome.

538
00:53:32,959 --> 00:53:35,837
You know, we're old and retired.

539
00:53:37,255 --> 00:53:42,552
We'd like to spend time
with our families in Canada,

540
00:53:42,636 --> 00:53:45,513
so we can't always look after Catherine.

541
00:53:46,014 --> 00:53:51,853
All our lives, we've been teaching.
Now we want to be with our families.

542
00:53:52,896 --> 00:53:55,815
If Catherine hadn't gotten sick,

543
00:53:56,566 --> 00:53:59,152
she'd still be teaching now.

544
00:54:01,863 --> 00:54:03,990
I remember you.

545
00:54:04,491 --> 00:54:11,206
You're the one who tried on
prom dresses in their house, right?

546
00:54:11,289 --> 00:54:14,292
But she wasn't able to go

547
00:54:14,376 --> 00:54:18,338
because Auntie Cielo died the next day.

548
00:54:18,421 --> 00:54:19,464
Yes.

549
00:54:29,432 --> 00:54:31,017
Angel, did you fart?

550
00:54:31,601 --> 00:54:32,811
No, silly.

551
00:54:33,353 --> 00:54:36,272
It stinks. I might throw up!

552
00:54:38,525 --> 00:54:39,901
Catherine…

553
00:54:42,696 --> 00:54:44,030
Did you poop?

554
00:54:44,781 --> 00:54:46,324
My goodness!

555
00:54:46,408 --> 00:54:49,119
- Angel, you have tissues?
- What the hell, Angel!

556
00:54:49,202 --> 00:54:51,997
- I just borrowed the van from Mommy!
- Tissue, please.

557
00:54:52,080 --> 00:54:52,914
I'm sorry.

558
00:54:52,998 --> 00:54:56,084
You could've told me to drive
to the gas station.

559
00:54:56,167 --> 00:54:58,461
You know she's sick.

560
00:54:58,545 --> 00:54:59,921
Can you park on the side?

561
00:55:00,588 --> 00:55:02,632
- Be careful!
- It's going to be wet.

562
00:55:03,383 --> 00:55:05,010
It stinks!

563
00:55:05,093 --> 00:55:08,596
You whine too much! I'm so sorry, Roger!

564
00:55:08,680 --> 00:55:09,889
Don't touch me!

565
00:55:09,973 --> 00:55:13,101
- Where are you going?
- I can't stand the stink!

566
00:55:15,562 --> 00:55:19,149
- We can stop somewhere to use a restroom.
- Angel!

567
00:55:19,232 --> 00:55:20,567
- What do we do about this?
- She pooped already.

568
00:55:20,650 --> 00:55:22,152
What could I have done?

569
00:55:22,902 --> 00:55:25,321
- I can't take it!
- I'll pay for the cleaning service.

570
00:55:25,405 --> 00:55:28,283
- You should have said something!
- Get in. You might get run over!

571
00:55:28,366 --> 00:55:30,368
- I really can't take it!
- Drive us home!

572
00:55:30,452 --> 00:55:33,288
- I need to wash Catherine!
- Don't touch me!

573
00:55:33,371 --> 00:55:35,248
- Don't touch me!
- Let's go home!

574
00:55:35,331 --> 00:55:37,667
- Hey! Let's go.
- No!

575
00:55:37,751 --> 00:55:39,461
How can I drive when I can't breathe?

576
00:55:39,544 --> 00:55:40,754
- Clean her up!
- Roger!

577
00:55:40,837 --> 00:55:42,088
- Help your grandma wipe that shit!
- I need to bathe Catherine!

578
00:55:42,172 --> 00:55:45,133
- Catherine needs to wash!
- Can we clean that if we're stuck here?

579
00:55:45,216 --> 00:55:47,761
Get in! I'll pay for your carwash.

580
00:55:47,844 --> 00:55:49,971
- I'm done!
- Get in the car!

581
00:55:50,055 --> 00:55:52,182
Calm down. Don't cry.

582
00:55:52,265 --> 00:55:53,975
Hey! Get in!

583
00:57:20,854 --> 00:57:24,524
More soap, so you'll feel fresh.

584
00:57:35,118 --> 00:57:36,703
It hurts!

585
00:57:55,847 --> 00:57:58,475
It hurts!

586
00:58:01,936 --> 00:58:03,188
It hurts!

587
00:58:03,271 --> 00:58:04,314
Ninay!

588
00:58:19,704 --> 00:58:20,997
It hurts!

589
00:58:22,290 --> 00:58:23,750
Ninay!

590
00:58:34,969 --> 00:58:35,845
Ninay!

591
00:58:36,554 --> 00:58:37,680
It hurts!

592
00:58:38,640 --> 00:58:39,807
Ninay!

593
00:58:45,647 --> 00:58:46,856
Ninay!

594
00:58:58,910 --> 00:59:00,828
Ninay!

595
00:59:07,710 --> 00:59:10,547
Grandma, why isn't Mom
the one caring for you?

596
00:59:12,924 --> 00:59:16,594
Oh, your mother is very busy.

597
00:59:18,555 --> 00:59:20,348
I'm content to have Ninay.

598
00:59:23,184 --> 00:59:24,894
And you're here.

599
00:59:28,106 --> 00:59:31,734
Yes, but Mom can give you better care,
since she's your daughter, right?

600
00:59:33,611 --> 00:59:36,906
Your mother and I,
we didn't develop a close relationship.

601
00:59:37,448 --> 00:59:39,492
Even as a child…

602
00:59:41,327 --> 00:59:43,037
she's been independent.

603
00:59:44,163 --> 00:59:46,249
It's as if she didn't need us.

604
00:59:48,543 --> 00:59:51,296
She grew up with me
and your grandpa bickering constantly.

605
00:59:54,257 --> 00:59:57,051
We couldn't give her enough love.

606
01:00:03,057 --> 01:00:04,642
Is that why she acts that way with Dad?

607
01:00:09,188 --> 01:00:10,356
Maybe.

608
01:00:13,526 --> 01:00:15,695
She wants to be alone.

609
01:00:20,074 --> 01:00:22,577
She prefers to survive on her own.

610
01:00:30,168 --> 01:00:31,294
Is that wrong?

611
01:00:36,341 --> 01:00:37,300
Not exactly.

612
01:00:40,803 --> 01:00:46,559
But our hearts should remain connected
to the people we love.

613
01:00:49,103 --> 01:00:54,359
Even if there's distance between us,
our ties should stay.

614
01:00:56,235 --> 01:00:59,155
It's not about the physical presence.

615
01:01:02,075 --> 01:01:07,914
True love lives in the heart
of the one you love,

616
01:01:09,123 --> 01:01:10,750
even if she's far away from you.

617
01:01:55,378 --> 01:01:56,546
Ninay.

618
01:01:59,674 --> 01:02:01,008
Ninay.

619
01:02:10,351 --> 01:02:11,686
Ninay.

620
01:02:14,897 --> 01:02:15,940
Ni--

621
01:02:16,941 --> 01:02:19,610
Has Catherine eaten?

622
01:02:20,111 --> 01:02:22,280
Yes, I've fed her.

623
01:02:23,030 --> 01:02:24,073
Where is she?

624
01:02:24,157 --> 01:02:25,283
She's there.

625
01:02:41,007 --> 01:02:41,966
Again!

626
01:02:44,302 --> 01:02:45,219
Hey!

627
01:02:53,478 --> 01:02:54,812
That's challenging.

628
01:02:55,980 --> 01:02:56,981
Again?

629
01:03:03,905 --> 01:03:05,114
Look at us!

630
01:03:09,702 --> 01:03:12,371
You're a better dancer than I am, Grandma!

631
01:03:46,197 --> 01:03:47,657
You need to eat.

632
01:03:48,616 --> 01:03:50,076
Swallow it.

633
01:03:51,077 --> 01:03:52,119
Say ah!

634
01:03:54,539 --> 01:03:55,581
Open up.

635
01:03:56,457 --> 01:03:58,709
That's it! Very good!

636
01:04:02,338 --> 01:04:04,048
More? Look at you.

637
01:04:07,134 --> 01:04:09,762
No more!

638
01:04:13,432 --> 01:04:14,267
‪I don't like.

639
01:04:30,074 --> 01:04:31,492
Are you full?

640
01:04:32,451 --> 01:04:33,411
You don't want to eat more?

641
01:04:35,872 --> 01:04:37,081
You've eaten enough?

642
01:04:47,300 --> 01:04:49,260
- We'll just dye
- What is that?

643
01:04:49,343 --> 01:04:53,222
- those white hairs of yours.
- Who are you?

644
01:04:54,765 --> 01:04:55,808
Ouch, it hurts!

645
01:04:56,434 --> 01:05:00,396
This will be quick. This won't hurt you.

646
01:05:00,479 --> 01:05:02,064
It hurts!

647
01:05:02,857 --> 01:05:03,900
Why do this?

648
01:05:04,650 --> 01:05:06,819
Who are you?

649
01:05:07,945 --> 01:05:09,363
Why?

650
01:05:09,447 --> 01:05:11,824
I said it hurts! Hurts so much!

651
01:05:11,908 --> 01:05:14,660
- It hurts! Stop it!
- Okay. No more.

652
01:05:14,744 --> 01:05:18,164
Stop it!

653
01:05:20,082 --> 01:05:25,504
Now there's a stain on the floor.
I'll wipe it.

654
01:05:25,588 --> 01:05:30,092
Who are you? Why are you doing this to me?

655
01:05:30,176 --> 01:05:32,219
- Wait a second.
- Who are you?

656
01:05:34,430 --> 01:05:37,350
No more!

657
01:05:37,433 --> 01:05:43,564
- Stop, I said.
- It hurts!

658
01:05:43,648 --> 01:05:45,274
- I'll stop, Catherine.
- It hurts!

659
01:05:45,358 --> 01:05:48,319
Stop it!

660
01:05:48,402 --> 01:05:50,947
Okay, I'll stop.

661
01:05:51,030 --> 01:05:53,491
Yes, it hurts.

662
01:05:53,574 --> 01:05:54,575
It hurts…

663
01:05:57,995 --> 01:05:59,497
Does it still hurt?

664
01:06:08,339 --> 01:06:09,548
Okay.

665
01:06:10,508 --> 01:06:11,717
Let's wash up.

666
01:07:07,273 --> 01:07:08,858
Catherine…

667
01:07:11,277 --> 01:07:13,279
You might not remember this,

668
01:07:14,488 --> 01:07:16,407
but I want to thank you.

669
01:07:21,162 --> 01:07:23,247
{\an8}The evening you came to my house

670
01:07:23,330 --> 01:07:25,916
{\an8}so I could try on the prom dress
you gave me,

671
01:07:27,376 --> 01:07:29,795
<i>and we spent the whole night together…</i>

672
01:07:31,130 --> 01:07:34,425
<i>That's the happiest day of my life.</i>

673
01:07:36,886 --> 01:07:40,139
<i>I felt how much you loved me,</i>

674
01:07:40,723 --> 01:07:42,767
<i>what we meant to each other.</i>

675
01:07:49,356 --> 01:07:52,276
I wanted to feel each second.

676
01:07:52,359 --> 01:07:54,737
I wished for time to stop.

677
01:07:55,529 --> 01:07:59,617
<i>So we could remain</i>
<i>in that embrace forever.</i>

678
01:08:08,250 --> 01:08:12,797
But that's the same hour
our world crumbled.

679
01:08:14,381 --> 01:08:16,675
<i>After that night,</i>

680
01:08:18,344 --> 01:08:21,263
<i>- my whole life changed.</i>
- I knew it!

681
01:08:21,347 --> 01:08:24,809
<i>- My father became cold towards me.</i>
- Animal!

682
01:08:25,893 --> 01:08:30,106
- I'm sorry, Dad!
- You brought shame to this house!

683
01:08:30,856 --> 01:08:32,316
You condoned this!

684
01:08:32,399 --> 01:08:38,906
<i>My mother fell ill,</i>
<i>and it led to her death.</i>

685
01:08:42,243 --> 01:08:46,080
<i>- My father blamed me for everything.</i>
- This is all your fault.

686
01:08:52,503 --> 01:08:55,381
<i>Even though they took me away from you,</i>

687
01:08:56,799 --> 01:08:59,260
<i>- not once did I forget you.</i>
- Your child is stubborn!

688
01:08:59,343 --> 01:09:00,553
Let's go!

689
01:09:00,636 --> 01:09:01,804
Catherine!

690
01:09:05,975 --> 01:09:07,935
<i>Your child is stubborn!</i>

691
01:09:09,603 --> 01:09:13,482
<i>Do you want us to lock you up?</i>
<i>Do you want us to send you to Mindoro?</i>

692
01:09:13,566 --> 01:09:17,528
<i>We'll send you to your relatives,</i>
<i>so that woman can't reach you!</i>

693
01:09:17,611 --> 01:09:22,449
<i>He married me off to Armando.</i>
<i>It produced a child.</i>

694
01:09:40,634 --> 01:09:43,470
Still, it's you who owned my heart.

695
01:09:52,104 --> 01:09:57,735
I never thought there'd come a time
when we'd meet again.

696
01:10:01,322 --> 01:10:03,866
But even if you don't remember,

697
01:10:06,994 --> 01:10:08,245
I know that…

698
01:10:09,872 --> 01:10:13,542
in your heart, you felt like I did.

699
01:10:15,419 --> 01:10:19,048
How much we loved each other.

700
01:10:27,598 --> 01:10:30,392
{\an8}LOVE POEMS
PABLO NERUDA

701
01:11:36,625 --> 01:11:37,668
Concha…

702
01:11:40,796 --> 01:11:42,006
Concha.

703
01:11:47,720 --> 01:11:48,721
Concha…

704
01:12:06,155 --> 01:12:07,197
Concha?

705
01:17:56,254 --> 01:18:01,385
<i>Why does the sun go on shining?</i>

706
01:18:03,011 --> 01:18:08,433
<i>Why does the sea rush to shore?</i>

707
01:18:09,851 --> 01:18:16,274
<i>Don't they know it's the end of the world?</i>

708
01:18:16,358 --> 01:18:21,822
<i>'Cause you don't love me anymore</i>

709
01:18:23,490 --> 01:18:28,954
<i>Why do the birds go on singing?</i>

710
01:18:30,288 --> 01:18:36,211
<i>Why do the stars glow above?</i>

711
01:18:37,087 --> 01:18:43,510
<i>Don't they know it's the end of the world?</i>

712
01:18:43,593 --> 01:18:49,558
<i>It ended when I lost your love</i>

713
01:18:50,350 --> 01:18:56,189
<i>I wake up in the morning and I wonder</i>

714
01:18:57,274 --> 01:19:02,904
<i>Why everything's the same as it was</i>

715
01:19:04,156 --> 01:19:10,871
<i>I can't understand, no, I can't understand</i>

716
01:19:10,954 --> 01:19:17,586
<i>How life goes on the way it does</i>

717
01:19:18,086 --> 01:19:23,675
<i>Why does my heart go on beating?</i>

718
01:19:24,926 --> 01:19:30,766
<i>Why do these eyes of mine cry?</i>

719
01:19:31,850 --> 01:19:37,981
<i>Don't they know it's the end of the world?</i>

720
01:19:38,482 --> 01:19:44,362
<i>It ended when you said goodbye</i>

721
01:20:46,758 --> 01:20:47,968
Catherine?

722
01:20:50,136 --> 01:20:51,429
Catherine?

723
01:20:55,559 --> 01:20:56,852
Concha?

724
01:20:57,811 --> 01:20:58,645
Hey!

725
01:20:59,229 --> 01:21:01,231
You're up so early.

726
01:21:01,314 --> 01:21:02,774
- You're working already!
- Look.

727
01:21:02,858 --> 01:21:05,360
- What happened?
- Poor bird.

728
01:21:06,403 --> 01:21:08,113
It fell.

729
01:21:08,947 --> 01:21:12,617
- What happened? Is it dead?
- It's injured.

730
01:21:13,535 --> 01:21:15,161
Poor thing.

731
01:21:17,289 --> 01:21:19,833
Come inside. You're probably tired.

732
01:21:19,916 --> 01:21:21,167
Come with me.

733
01:22:27,609 --> 01:22:28,902
Who are you?

734
01:24:00,702 --> 01:24:02,287
You're right, Grandma, it's beautiful.

735
01:24:03,163 --> 01:24:04,372
It fits me perfectly.

736
01:24:23,141 --> 01:24:24,434
What should I do now?

737
01:24:27,687 --> 01:24:28,855
You're already gone.

738
01:24:37,697 --> 01:24:39,074
What happens to me now?

739
01:24:44,496 --> 01:24:46,456
Where do I go?

740
01:24:52,128 --> 01:24:54,255
Nobody wants me.

741
01:24:59,552 --> 01:25:02,013
What happens to me and Grandma Catherine?

742
01:25:14,025 --> 01:25:16,486
I don't know what to do, Grandma.

743
01:25:27,789 --> 01:25:28,998
Grandma…

744
01:25:31,126 --> 01:25:33,378
Just don't forsake me.

745
01:25:35,004 --> 01:25:36,840
I can't do this alone.

746
01:25:40,802 --> 01:25:46,975
Please continue guiding me, all right?

747
01:25:55,942 --> 01:25:57,318
Even if it's hard,

748
01:26:00,488 --> 01:26:04,534
I will try to wake up every day for you.

749
01:26:08,288 --> 01:26:13,418
I will choose
to be a good person because of you.

750
01:27:03,051 --> 01:27:06,638
Embarrassing. Our guests had to wait!
Are you going to be fine?

751
01:27:10,475 --> 01:27:12,352
Uncle! You're here.

752
01:27:17,607 --> 01:27:19,317
Traffic's crazy.

753
01:27:22,362 --> 01:27:23,655
Hi.

754
01:27:23,738 --> 01:27:26,282
You've been waiting a while? I'm sorry.

755
01:27:26,908 --> 01:27:28,660
Traffic's crazy.

756
01:27:28,743 --> 01:27:30,620
Have some snacks, please.

757
01:27:31,746 --> 01:27:34,374
Please serve them drinks. It's so hot.

758
01:27:35,750 --> 01:27:37,877
Angel.

759
01:27:38,461 --> 01:27:40,964
Tell Ninay to serve the food, okay?

760
01:27:41,047 --> 01:27:44,133
The guests are arriving from the funeral.

761
01:27:48,471 --> 01:27:51,057
Are you guys comfortable?

762
01:27:51,933 --> 01:27:54,852
I'll send some food for you.

763
01:27:54,936 --> 01:27:56,437
Attend to them too, please.

764
01:27:57,522 --> 01:27:58,982
Hey, Raymund!

765
01:28:00,358 --> 01:28:01,401
because our flight got delayed.

766
01:28:05,613 --> 01:28:07,740
Raymund's here.

767
01:28:13,496 --> 01:28:14,622
Take a seat.

768
01:28:21,879 --> 01:28:23,423
Who else is here?

769
01:28:24,299 --> 01:28:26,175
There's Uncle William…

770
01:28:26,718 --> 01:28:27,802
Grandma Ninay…

771
01:28:28,428 --> 01:28:29,387
Grandma Ninay…

772
01:29:33,159 --> 01:29:34,577
<i>Catherine!</i>

773
01:29:40,958 --> 01:29:42,668
<i>Stop this madness!</i>

774
01:29:42,752 --> 01:29:44,921
<i>Catherine!</i>

775
01:29:46,756 --> 01:29:49,175
<i>You! You've condoned them!</i>

776
01:29:49,258 --> 01:29:51,219
<i>Catherine!</i>

777
01:29:53,971 --> 01:29:57,058
<i>Your child is stubborn,</i>
<i>won't accept discipline!</i>

778
01:29:57,642 --> 01:29:58,976
<i>Do you want us to lock you up?</i>

779
01:29:59,060 --> 01:30:01,437
<i>Do you want us to send you to Mindoro?</i>

780
01:30:01,521 --> 01:30:04,857
<i>We'll take you to your relatives,</i>
<i>where that woman can't reach you!</i>

781
01:30:05,399 --> 01:30:06,567
<i>Catherine!</i>

782
01:30:46,732 --> 01:30:49,110
Don't worry, Grandma Catherine.

783
01:30:50,653 --> 01:30:52,113
I'll be here for you.

784
01:30:53,990 --> 01:30:55,825
I'll take care of you.

785
01:30:57,952 --> 01:31:00,788
I am sure that is what my grandmother
would have wanted.

786
01:31:05,042 --> 01:31:07,253
I will never abandon you.

787
01:31:11,048 --> 01:31:13,009
This is not a sacrifice,

788
01:31:14,218 --> 01:31:15,720
but a service,

789
01:31:17,847 --> 01:31:21,017
and a way to thank you,
because the two of you showed me

790
01:31:24,478 --> 01:31:27,440
what true love is.

791
01:31:52,006 --> 01:31:53,090
Who are you?

792
01:31:55,051 --> 01:31:56,219
My name is Angel.

793
01:31:56,886 --> 01:31:58,471
- Angel wants you to eat.
- Who are you?

794
01:31:58,554 --> 01:31:59,305
Please?

795
01:31:59,388 --> 01:32:01,849
- Enough.
- Angel wants you to eat.

796
01:32:02,350 --> 01:32:04,101
No more, no!

797
01:32:06,562 --> 01:32:07,730
No more!

798
01:32:08,397 --> 01:32:10,441
That's enough!

799
01:32:10,524 --> 01:32:11,943
Who are you?

800
01:32:14,153 --> 01:32:15,321
Let's take this off.

801
01:32:18,282 --> 01:32:19,492
Who are you?

802
01:32:22,036 --> 01:32:23,162
I'm Angel.

803
01:32:24,455 --> 01:32:25,748
Who are you?

804
01:32:31,462 --> 01:32:32,797
Angel.

805
01:35:02,863 --> 01:35:04,031
Oh!

806
01:35:43,988 --> 01:35:45,072
Grandma Catherine…

807
01:35:46,907 --> 01:35:48,242
Grandma…

808
01:35:48,325 --> 01:35:49,577
Let's eat.

809
01:35:51,245 --> 01:35:52,413
Grandma Catherine…

810
01:35:54,081 --> 01:35:55,124
Grandma…

811
01:36:00,171 --> 01:36:01,130
Grandma…

812
01:36:06,760 --> 01:36:07,720
Grandma…

813
01:36:10,097 --> 01:36:11,265
Grandma Catherine…

814
01:36:15,644 --> 01:36:16,479
Grandma…

815
01:37:31,595 --> 01:37:33,097
Granny, do you need help crossing?

816
01:37:33,889 --> 01:37:36,559
We'll walk with you.
The signal says "go" now.

817
01:37:36,642 --> 01:37:37,935
Let's cross.

818
01:37:38,018 --> 01:37:39,186
Thank you.

819
01:37:39,979 --> 01:37:42,022
Don't be afraid. We can walk now.

820
01:37:42,106 --> 01:37:43,941
Let's cross now, Granny.

821
01:37:44,483 --> 01:37:45,568
Let's go.

822
01:38:07,590 --> 01:38:10,301
- Dad, you promised me.
- All right, anytime.

823
01:38:10,384 --> 01:38:13,470
Just make sure you focus on your studies.

824
01:38:13,554 --> 01:38:15,472
- That's right.
- I will.

825
01:38:15,556 --> 01:38:18,017
Cebu will always be there
if you want to visit.

826
01:38:18,100 --> 01:38:19,018
All right.

827
01:38:19,101 --> 01:38:22,396
- When you're ready, we will go there.
- Mom's here.

828
01:38:22,479 --> 01:38:23,981
Okay. Okay.

829
01:38:28,652 --> 01:38:30,487
- Hi.
- Hi, Uncle.

830
01:38:33,115 --> 01:38:37,202
I heard your vacation was great.
Thank you for taking care of Angel.

831
01:38:37,286 --> 01:38:38,412
Of course.

832
01:38:38,495 --> 01:38:40,706
When can we have dinner together?

833
01:38:41,290 --> 01:38:43,876
Whenever you're available.
We're free anytime.

834
01:38:43,959 --> 01:38:46,587
We'll message you.
I'm sure we'll find a common schedule.

835
01:38:46,670 --> 01:38:47,588
All right.

836
01:38:47,671 --> 01:38:49,214
Go on, Dad! I might be late for class.

837
01:38:49,298 --> 01:38:51,050
- I love you.
- Take care.

838
01:38:51,133 --> 01:38:53,761
- Study hard, okay?
- Yes, I will!

839
01:38:58,515 --> 01:38:59,350
- How are you, Mom?
- Had fun?

840
01:38:59,433 --> 01:39:01,644
- Yes, super fun!
- That's good, baby!

841
01:39:07,191 --> 01:39:08,651
Here's your money.

842
01:39:10,069 --> 01:39:12,821
Let me know if you need anything else.

843
01:39:12,905 --> 01:39:16,200
That should be enough. Don't lose it.

844
01:39:16,283 --> 01:39:18,869
Hey, don't miss our dinner.

845
01:39:18,952 --> 01:39:19,912
- All right!
- I'll pick you up.

846
01:39:19,995 --> 01:39:21,413
Really? Sure.

847
01:39:21,955 --> 01:39:23,415
- I'll see you again?
- Of course.

848
01:39:25,250 --> 01:39:26,543
- Bye, Uncle.
- Study well!

849
01:39:26,627 --> 01:39:28,128
- I will.
- Bye!

